DURBAN - Health MEC Dr Sibongiseni Dhlomo has urged the relatives of the more than 50 flood victims to identify the bodies of their loved ones at the city mortuaries.
He said that at Pinetown Medico-Legal Mortuary, the bodies of 36 people were being kept. They were taken in from Chatsworth, Malvern, Mariannhill and surrounding areas. 

Meanwhile, the Magwaza Maphalala (Gale) Street Medico-Legal Mortuary has the bodies of 15 people which were brought in from uMlazi, Reservoir Hills, Overport, Bluff and surrounding areas.
Dhlomo said that members of the clergy and social workers would be available to provide counselling and other psycho-social support services for the bereaved families.
“This is an extremely difficult time, but we have put these measures in place to help people,” Dhlomo said.  

 
 
